rComments: She's pretty laid back. Attending class is a huge must when learning a language. The exams and quizzes are fair, no trick questions and pretty easy if you study. The work load is super manageable. The lectures can be a bit boring as she does not waste any time and fills it with theory for the entire hour fifteen.
Her lectures are very interesting, she uses a lot of humour and interacts well with students. She is very nice and helpful!
Pretty good overall but sometimes singles people out in class to answer questions randomly and uses negatvie marking.
